latestPosts.caption:
Hey lovelies✨
I'd been noticing the hike of scams and delayed payments among nano creators lately, and I thought I could share a few tips that came in handy for me:)

👉Please note- this may not be the best strategy, I rejected almost every reimbursement collaboration. While it costed me several opportunities or quick exposure, it saved me from unnecessary confusion and stress of getting repaid. (For me, it was worth it. It preserved my mental health😅😂)

👉Over time, I was able to build the reach and followers, so brands began offering me barter collaborations. 

👉As budding creators, I understand we'd have to take risks to get a breakthrough. Make informed decisions, not hasty ones, and focus on building on your content. 

👉Understand the pros and cons before taking up any offer. 
These are my personal tips, so take it or feel free to leave it, choose what works for you, restrategise, and move ahead in your content creation journey!

Comment for any queries, or if you want a part 2. I'm happy to help! 

#contentcreator #ugc #contentmarketing #scam #fraud #brands #digitalmarketing #staysafe #cybercrime
